This paper is about evaluating metrics for search engine results, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper focuses on predicting user preferences, which is a topic within Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The evaluation of metrics also involves analyzing the relevance of search results, which is a topic within Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the impact of considering more results on the performance of metrics, which could be relevant to the field of Cybersecurity (cs.CR) or Cybernetics (cs.CY).
